A.4.3.2-1/4a.description: Support 256QAM for PUSCH for at least one NR FR2 band

A.4.3.2-1/13.description: Supports supplemental uplink with dynamic switch (DCI based selection of PUSCH carrier)

A.4.3.2-1/14.description: Supports MIMO layers at the UE for PUSCH transmission with codebook precoding. UE indicating support of this feature shall also indicate support of PUSCH codebook coherency subset

A.4.3.2-1/16.description: Support receiving PDSCH with interleaved VRB-to-PRB mapping

A.4.3.2-1/17.description: Support dynamic EN-DC power sharing for at least one EN-DC band combination_FR1 only

A.4.3.2-1/18.description: Supports up to 10 search spaces in a SCell per BWP

A.4.3.2-1/19.description: Supports spatial bundling of HARQ-ACK bits carried on PUCCH or PUSCH per PUCCH group. With spatial bundling, two HARQ-ACK bits for a DL MIMO data is bundled into a single bit by logical "AND" operation

A.4.3.2-1/20.description: Support alternative additional DMRS position for co-existence with LTE CRS

A.4.3.2-1/21.description: Supports transmitting PUSCH scheduled by DCI format 0_0 or 0_1 when configured with higher layer parameter aggregationFactorIUL > 1

A.4.3.2-1/22.description: Support beam correspondence without UL beam sweeping

A.4.3.2-1/22A.description: Support beam correspondence based on SSB

A.4.3.2-1/22B.description: Support beam correspondence based on CSI-RS

A.4.3.2-1/23.description: The maximum number of spatial multiplexing layer(s) supported by the UE for DL reception is 8 Layers. For single CC standalone NR, it is mandatory with capability signalling to support at least 4 MIMO layers in the bands where 4Rx is specified as mandatory for the given UE and at least 2 MIMO layers in FR2. If absent, the UE doesnt support MIMO on this carrier

A.4.3.2-1/23A.description: The maximum number of spatial multiplexing layer(s) supported by the UE for DL reception is 4 Layers.

A.4.3.2-1/23B.description: The maximum number of spatial multiplexing layer(s) supported by the UE for DL reception is 2 Layers.

A.4.3.2-1/24.description: Supports DCI and timer based active BWP switching delay type1

A.4.3.2-1/24A.description: Supports DCI and timer based active BWP switching delay type2

A.4.3.2-1/24B.description: Supports incremental delay for DCI and timer based active BWP switching type 1 on multiple CCs simultaneously

A.4.3.2-1/24C.description: Supports incremental delay for DCI and timer based active BWP switching type 2 on multiple CCs simultaneously

A.4.3.2-1/26.description: Support dynamic switching between resource allocation Types 0 and 1 for PDSCH

A.4.3.2-1/27.description: Support dynamic switching between resource allocation Types 0 and 1 for PUSCH

A.4.3.2-1/28.description: Support almost contiguous UL CP-OFDM transmissions in FR1

A.4.3.2-1/29.description: Support almost contiguous UL CP-OFDM transmissions in FR2

A.4.3.2-1/30.description: Support dynamic indication of applicable minimum scheduling restriction by DCI format 0_1 and 1_1, and the minimum scheduling offset for PDSCH and aperiodic CSI-RS triggering offset (K0), and PUSCH (K2), and the extended value range for aperiodic CSI-RS triggering offset

A.4.3.2-1/31.description: Supports pi/2-BPSK modulation scheme for PUSCH in FR1

A.4.3.2-1/31a.description: Supports pi/2-BPSK modulation scheme for PUSCH in FR2

A.4.3.2-1/32.description: Support multi-DCI based multi-TRP and support of fully/partially overlapping PDSCHs in time and non-overlapping in frequency

A.4.3.2-1/33.description: Support receiving PDSCH with resource mapping that excludes the REs determined by the higher layer configuration LTE-carrier configuring common RS

A.4.3.2-1/34.description: Support of BWP operation without bandwidth restriction

A.4.3.2-1/35.description: Support of receiving SCell dormancy indication on SPCell using DCI format 2_6 outside the active time

A.4.3.2-1/36.description: Supports pi/2-BPSK modulation scheme for power boosting in FR1

A.4.3.2-1/37.description: Support of dynamic 1Tx-2Tx UL Tx switching

A.4.3.2-1/37a.description: Support of 35us Tx switching period for 1Tx-2Tx UL Tx switching

A.4.3.2-1/37b.description: Support of 140us Tx switching period for 1Tx-2Tx UL Tx switching

A.4.3.2-1/37c.description: 210us Tx switching period for 1Tx-2Tx UL Tx switching

A.4.3.2-1/37d.description: Support of DL interruption during 1Tx-2Tx UL Tx switching

A.4.3.2-1/38.description: Support uplink transmission power boost by suspension of in-band emission (IBE) in FR2

A.4.3.2-1/39.description: Supports the alternative 64QAM MCS table for PDSCH

A.4.3.2-1/40.description: Supports the CQI table with target BLER of 10^-5

A.4.3.2-1/41.description: Supports of single DCI based spatial division multiplexing scheme

A.4.3.2-1/42.description: Support of BWP adaptation (up to 2 BWPs) with the same numerology for FR1 FDD bands

A.4.3.2-1/42a.description: Support of BWP adaptation (up to 2 BWPs) with the same numerology for FR1 TDD bands

A.4.3.2-1/42b.description: Support of BWP adaptation (up to 2 BWPs) with the same numerology for FR2 bands

A.4.3.2-1/43.description: Support of BWP adaptation (up to 4 BWPs) with the same numerology for FR1 FDD bands

A.4.3.2-1/43a.description: Support of BWP adaptation (up to 4 BWPs) with the same numerology for FR1 TDD bands

A.4.3.2-1/43b.description: Support of BWP adaptation (up to 4 BWPs) with the same numerology for FR2 bands

A.4.3.2-1/44a.description: Support BWP adaptation up to 4 BWPs with the different numerologies, via DCI and timer for FR1 TDD bands

A.4.3.2-1/44b.description: Support BWP adaptation up to 4 BWPs with the different numerologies, via DCI and timer for FR2 bands

A.4.3.2-1/52.description: Support monitoring DCI format 1_2 for DL scheduling and monitoring DCI format 0_2 for UL scheduling

A.4.3.2-1/54.description: Support of single DCI based FDMSchemeA

A.4.3.2-1/55.description: Support of single-DCI based inter-slot TDM

A.4.3.2-1/56.description: Support of maximum number of TRS resource sets per CC which the UE can track simultaneously is at least 2

A.4.3.2-1/60.description: Support of UL full power transmission mode of fullpowerMode2

A.4.3.2-1/69.description: Support of FDD NR UL transmission with a 7.5 kHz shift to the LTE raster

A.4.3.2-1/72.description: Support of SSB/CSI-RS for L1-SINR measurement

A.4.3.2-1/76.description: Support of CSI-RS as CMR without dedicated IMR configured for L1-SINR measurement

A.4.3.2-1/77.description: Support of SCell beam failure recovery

A.4.3.2-1/78.description: Support of the maximum number of activated TCI states per BWP per CC is other than n1, including control and data

A.4.3.2-1/79.description: Support enhanced UL performance for the transient period

A.4.3.2-1/81.description: Supports the priority indicator field configured in DCI formats 0_1 and 0_2 in a BWP when configured to monitor both DCI formats 0_1 and 0_2 in the BWP

A.4.3.2-1/92.description: Support of NTN features in NGSO scenario

A.4.3.2-1/95.description: Supports the restriction to 3450 - 3650 MHz and 3650 - 3980 ranges of band n77

A.4.3.2-1/105.description: Support of 1024QAM modulation scheme for PDSCH with maximum 2 MIMO layers for FR1 TDD bands

A.4.3.2-1/107.description: Support of 1024QAM modulation scheme for PDSCH for FR1_TDD bands

A.4.3.2-1/134.description: Indicates whether UE supports partial frequency sounding for SRS with frequency hopping.

A.4.3.2-1/135.description: Indicates whether the UE supports partial frequency sounding for SRS with frequency hopping and start RB location hopping.

A.4.3.2-1/136.description: Indicates whether the UE supports PDCCH search space monitoring occasions in any symbol of the slot (pdcch-MonitoringAnyOccasions)

A.4.3.2-1/137.description: Indicates whether the UE supports PDCCH search space monitoring occasions in any symbol of the slot with minimum time separation between two onsecutive transmissions of PDCCH with span (pdcch-MonitoringAnyOccasionsWithSpanGap)

A.4.3.2-1/138.description: Support of UE reporting of information related to TA pre-compensation

A.4.3.2-1/139.description: Indicates whether the UE supports mTRP BFR based on two BFD-RS sets.

A.4.3.2-1/140.description: Indicates the support of intra-slot PDCCH repetition based on two linked SS sets associated with corresponding CORESETs.

A.4.3.2-1/141.description: Support of reception of UE-specific K_offset

A.4.3.2-1/143.description: Indicates whether UE supports multi-TRP PUSCH repetition based on codebook with PUSCH repetition type A.

A.4.3.2-1/144.description: Indicates whether UE supports multi-TRP PUSCH repetition based on codebook with PUSCH repetition type B.

A.4.3.2-1/145.description: Indicates whether UE supports cyclic mapping when the number of repetitions is larger than 2 with repetition type.

A.4.3.2-1/146.description: Indicates whether UE supports PHR reporting related to M-TRP PUSCH repetition (calculate two PHRs (at least corresponding to the CC that applies m-TRP PUSCH repetitions), each associated with a first PUSCH occasion corresponding to each SRS resource set, and report two PHRs).

A.4.3.2-1/147.description: Indicates whether UE supports DM-RS bundling for PUCCH repetitions for PUCCH formats 1/3/4 over consecutive symbols

A.4.3.2-1/148.description: Indicates whether UE supports DM-RS bundling for TB processing over multi-slot PUSCH over consecutive symbols

A.4.3.2-1/149.description: Indicates whether the UE supports DM-RS bundling for PUSCH repetition type A over consecutive symbols

A.4.3.2-1/150.description: Indicates whether the UE supports DM-RS bundling for PUSCH repetition type B over consecutive symbols

A.4.3.2-1/151.description:
Indicates whether the UE supports 3 MHz symmetric channel bandwidth in DL and UL, including the following functional components:
-	Reception of 12 PRB PBCH based on RB-level puncturing;
-	Short RACH preamble formats with 15kHz SCS, and long PRACH formats with 1.25kHz SCS;
-	Reception of 15 PRB CORESET0.
This feature is supported for 15kHz SCS only. It is applicable only to single-carrier operation and when an associated SS/PBCH block is located according to Table 5.4.3.3-2 in TS 38.101-1 [2].

This feature is not applicable to UEs indicating supportOfRedCap-r17 or supportOfERedCap-r18.

NOTE:	The UE supporting this capability supports configuration of 15 PRB BWP operation in DL and UL.

A.4.3.2-1/152.description:
Indicates whether the UE supports reception of 12 PRB CORESET0 with an associated SS/PBCH block that is located according to Table 5.4.3.1-2 in TS 38.101-1 [2].
A UE supporting this feature shall also indicate support of support-3MHz-ChannelBW-Symmetric-r18.
This feature is supported for 15kHz SCS only.
This feature is only applicable to single-carrier operation.

This feature is not applicable to UEs indicating supportOfRedCap-r17 or supportOfERedCap-r18.

NOTE:	The UE supporting this capability supports configuration of 12 PRB BWP operation.

A.4.3.2-1/153.description: Support of 35us Tx switching period for 2Tx-2Tx dynamic UL Tx switching

A.4.3.2-1/154.description: Support of 140us Tx switching period for 2Tx-2Tx dynamic UL Tx switching

A.4.3.2-1/155.description: Support of 210us Tx switching period for 2Tx-2Tx dynamic UL Tx switching

A.4.3.2-1/156.description: Support of DL interruption during 2Tx-2Tx dynamic UL Tx switching

A.4.3.2-1/157.description: Indicates the interruption time on DL/UL reception within a NR band pair during the RF retuning for switching between a carrier on one band and another (PUSCH-less) carrier on the other band to transmit SRS

A.4.3.2-1/158.description: Indicates the interruption time on DL/UL reception within a EUTRA band pair during the RF retuning for switching between a carrier on one band and another (PUSCH-less) carrier on the other band to transmit SRS

A.4.3.2-1/159.description: Indicates whether the UE supports multi-PUSCHs for configured grant by indicating whether the UE supports the determination of time-domain resource allocation for CG-PUSCHs associated to a multi-PUSCHs CG

A.4.3.2-1/160.description: Supports {2, 4, 8} for the number of multiple PRACH transmissions with same Tx spatial filter.

A.4.3.2-1/162.description: Indicates whether the UE supports monitoring DCI format 1_3 for DL scheduling with same SCS between scheduling cell and cells in the set and supports Type-2 for 'Antenna port(s)' field.

A.4.3.2-1/163.description: Indicates whether the UE supports monitoring DCI format 0_3 for UL scheduling with same SCS between scheduling cell and cells in the set and supports Type-2 for 'Antenna port(s)', 'Precoding information and number of layers' and 'SRS resource indicator' fields.

A.4.3.2-1/164.description: Indicates whether the UE supports co-scheduled cell indication scheme based on FDRA field of DCI format 1_3.

A.4.3.2-1/165.description: Indicates whether the UE supports co-scheduled cell indication scheme based on Scheduled cell set indicator field of DCI format 1_3

A.4.3.2-1/166.description: Indicates whether the UE supports co-scheduled cell indication scheme based on FDRA field of DCI format 0_3.

A.4.3.2-1/167.description: Indicates whether the UE supports co-scheduled cell indication scheme based on Scheduled cell set indicator field of DCI format 0_3

A.4.3.2-1/168.description: Indicate whether the UE supports search space set configurations for DCI format 1_3 for the set of cells with the same searchSpaceId are provided on both the scheduling cell and a serving cell in the set of cells with the scheduling cell being in the set of cells.

A.4.3.2-1/169.description: Indicate whether the UE supports search space set configurations for DCI format 0_3 for the set of cells with the same searchSpaceId are provided on both the scheduling cell and a serving cell in the set of cells with the scheduling cell being in the set of cells.

A.4.3.2-1/170.description: Indicates whether the UE supports harq feedback type1 for DCI format 1_3

A.4.3.2-1/171.description: Indicates whether the UE supports harq feedback type2 for DCI format 1_3

A.4.3.2-1/172.description: Indicates whether the UE supports basic feature of Rel-18 enhanced DMRS ports for PDSCH for scheduling of mapping type A.

A.4.3.2-1/173.description:
Indicates whether the UE supports unified TCI with separate DL/UL TCI update for single-DCI based intra-cell multi-TRP with multiple activated TCI codepoints per CC.
TCI state indication for update and activation includes:
-    MAC-CE+DCI-based TCI state indication (use of monitored DCI formats 1_1 and if supported 1_2) with DL assignment;
-    MAC-CE+DCI-based TCI state indication (use of monitored DCI formats 1_1 and if supported 1_2) without DL assignment.
The capability signalling comprises the following parameters:
-    maxNumActiveDL-TCI-AcrossCC-r18 indicates the maximum number of activated DL TCI states across all CCs,
-    maxNumActiveUL-TCI-AcrossCC-r18 indicates the maximum number of activated UL TCI states across all CCs.

A.4.3.2-1/174.description:
Indicates whether the UE supports two TA enhancement for multi-DCI based intra-cell Multi-TRP operation.
A UE supporting this feature shall also indicate support of multiDCI-MultiTRP-r16.

A.4.3.2-1/175.description: Support unified TCI with joint DL/UL LTM TCI-state indication for LTM procedure, indicating and activating a single joint LTM TCI state in a cell switch command

A.4.3.2-1/176.description: Support unified TCI with separate DL/UL TCI-state indication for LTM procedure and indicating/activating a pair of UL/DL TCI-state in a cell switch command

A.4.3.2-1/177.description: Support fast processing of LTM candidate cell RRC configuration

A.4.3.2-1/178.description: Support MAC-CE activated joint LTM TCI states

A.4.3.2-1/179.description: Support MAC-CE activated DL/UL LTM TCI states

A.4.3.2-1/181.description: Support TA indication in cell switch command

A.4.3.2-1/182.description: Support UE-based TA measurement by indicating the maximum number of candidate cells that the UE maintains the TA for

A.4.3.2-1/183.description: Support PDCCH-ordered RACH transmission for the corresponding band pair indicating whether UE may cause interruption on DL slot(s) on serving cells due to PDCCH-ordered RACH transmission

A.4.3.2-1/184.description: Support PDCCH-ordered RACH transmission for the corresponding band pair indicating the RF/BB preparation time for PDCCH ordered RACH of which the resources are not fully contained in any of UE's configured UL BWP(s) of active serving cells

A.4.3.2-1/185.description: Support PDCCH-ordered RACH transmission for the corresponding band pair indicating the interruption length (Y ms) due to RF re-tuning for PDCCH ordered RACH of which the resources are not fully contained in any of UE's configured UL BWP(s) of active serving cells

A.4.3.2-1/186.description: Support simultaneous transmission to handle the overlap between UL transmission on serving cell(s) and PRACH on candidate cell(s)

A.4.3.2-1/187.description: Indicates whether the UE supports cell DTX operation by RRC configuration

A.4.3.2-1/188.description: Indicates whether the UE supports cell DRX operation by RRC configuration

A.4.3.2-1/189.description: Indicates whether the UE supports cell DTX/DRX configuration activation and deactivation via DCI 2_9

A.4.3.2-1/190.description: Indicates whether the UE supports R-ML (reduced complexity ML) receivers with enhanced inter-user interference suppression, when co-scheduled UE(s)' modulation order is explicitly signalled by DCI.
